# $Header: /var/cvsroot/gentoo-x86/x11-terms/mlterm/ChangeLog,v 1.22 2003/12/05 08:15:29 usata Exp $

  05 Dec 2003; Mamoru KOMACHI <usata@gentoo.org> mlterm-2.6.3-r2.ebuild,
  mlterm-2.7.0-r1.ebuild, mlterm-2.8.0_p1-r1.ebuild:
  Removed deprecated : operator.

  30 Nov 2003; Mamoru KOMACHI <usata@gentoo.org> mlterm-2.6.3-r2.ebuild,
  mlterm-2.7.0-r1.ebuild, mlterm-2.8.0_p1-r1.ebuild:
  Corrected DEPEND. Removed nopixbuf IUSE flag. (mlterm uses either
  imlib, gdk-pixbuf1 or gdk-pixbuf2, so there's no good reason for
  associating nopixbuf with gdk-pixbuf1 and making it default)
  Closing bug #34573

  01 Nov 2003; Mamoru KOMACHI <usata@gentoo.org> mlterm-2.6.3-r1.ebuild,
  mlterm-2.6.3-r2.ebuild, mlterm-2.6.3.ebuild, mlterm-2.7.0.ebuild,
  mlterm-2.8.0.ebuild:
  Cleaned out duplicate versions

*mlterm-2.8.0_p1-r1 (27 Oct 2003)

  30 Nov 2003; Mamoru KOMACHI <usata@gentoo.org> mlterm-2.8.0_p1-r1.ebuild:
  Marked as stable

  27 Oct 2003; Masatomo Nakano <nakano@gentoo.org> mlterm-2.8.0_p1-r1.ebuild:
  Fixed ebuild bug in which some documents are not installed

*mlterm-2.8.0_p1 (20 Oct 2003)

  27 Oct 2003; Masatomo Nakano <nakano@gentoo.org> mlterm-2.8.0_p1.ebuild:
  Marked stable on x86/ppc

  20 Oct 2003; Masatomo Nakano <nakano@gentoo.org> mlterm-2.8.0_p1.ebuild:
  Modified to apply a bug fix patch. Thanks to Sadayuki Kobayashi
  <desperado@s17.xrea.com>. closed #31547.

